# Alembic migrations

Connection URL is **not** stored in `alembic.ini`. It comes from `auto_assign.db.session.get_database_url()` (loads `.env`: `DATABASE_URL` or `POSTGRES_*`).

## Commands (from repo root)

```bash
# Apply all migrations to your database (e.g. Postgres from .env)
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Create a new revision after changing ORM models
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe_change"

# Roll back one revision
uv run alembic downgrade -1
```

Use the same `.env` as the app so migrations target the same Postgres instance.
